            <h3 class="preschools-title AvantGarde">PRESCHOOLS OF THE FUTURE</h3>
            <p class="preschools-p p AvantGarde">There are 12 million rural children without preschool education in China, and about 20 million children in China without quality preschool education. Early education plays a vital role in people’s later adult life, and is the most cost effective way to improve the living conditions of people in poor and backward areas.</p>
            <p class="preschools-p p AvantGarde">This is the reason why we established the Rural Early Childhood Development Education Fund (REED). Donors of REED are business elites in China and elsewhere.</p>
            <p class="preschools-p p AvantGarde">REED started the first six preschool classes for children aged 3 to 6 in Butuo County, Sichuan, in 2014. Today we run 100 classes in 60 villages in the county. We train, manage and support the 200 teachers who teach and care for the students of those 100 classes in Butuo County, Liangshan Prefecture in a very close cooperation with the government and Bureau of Education, Sports and Science and Technology of Butuo County. Over 4,500 children get to preschool every day, get a solid meal and high-quality early education that will help them get a good start in life. Learning Mandarin is particularly important for minority children, like the Yi Minority children in Butuo.</p>
            <p class="preschools-p p AvantGarde">Shanghai Huji Foundation is doing the actual work, implementing the "Preschool of the Future" concept in the local area. The concept employs modern child-centered early education while following the guidelines of the PRC Ministry of Education for preschools, improving the quality of preschools in remote rural villages. REED is very proud to work closely together with Shanghai Huji Foundation team working side by side with the children, the parents and the teachers in their villages.</p>
            <p class="preschools-p p AvantGarde">Many more children are in need of such support. We welcome more government agencies, partners, parents and community organizations to work together on early childhood education in remote areas.</p>
